In view of the foregoing, we recommended that Management:

Require the City Accountant to identify the existence of the Registry of Public Infrastructure which includes all local road networks implemented by the City Government prior to the implementation of PPSAS;

Create an Inventory Committee who shall be responsible in the conduct of physical inventory of local road networks funded by the City Government; 

Direct the City Accountant to comply with the target recognition of local road networks in the books of accounts which is expected to be 100% fully recognized by the year 2019; 

 Require the General Service Officer and the City Engineer to prepare a list of road inventory and its vicinity map for easy identification during and after the physical inventory and;

Ensure that road components (road lot, pavements, drainage and slope, etc.) are  indicated in the road network ledger and property cards maintained by the City Accountant and General Service Officer

We have recommended that management shall:

Stop the purchase of mobile phones and tablets of expensive brands apparently considered as unnecessary and excessive expenditures to avoid disallowance in audit;

Limit the issuance of mobile phones to only one per qualified official up to Division Chief rank or higher;

Require the City Officials who are issued with more than one unit of mobile phones to surrender or pay the remaining book value of the said asset;

Demand from the Former City Councilors to surrender the mobile phones issued under their accountability so that they may not be held liable for Malversation of Public Property.

