Based on the foregoing, we recommended that the management should:
Specify the consultants’ duties/functions in the contracts as bases in the enforcement of their deliverables with the end in view to maximizing the worth of hiring said consultants and job orders and minimizing monetary losses to the City;
Consider the desired expertise, which is not available among the regular staff, in hiring consultants;
Evaluate and utilize the skills and talents of their regular employees to cut cost and to boost their morale;
Require the submission of accomplishment reports as basis for payment (not stereotype report).  Utilize the services of the permanent employees in discharging regular/ordinary services to compensate and maximize  the costs of their employment;
Revisit its organizational structure, staffing pattern and service requirements to assess the necessity of hiring consultants; and
Explain/justify why the hiring of consultants and job orders should not be stopped.
Based on the foregoing, we recommended that the management should:
Specify the duties/functions of the job order employees in the contracts as bases in the enforcement of their deliverables with the end in view to maximizing the worth of hiring said job orders and minimizing monetary losses to the City.
Refrain from hiring Job Orders/Contract of Services unless these are necessary in the implementation of the local projects. Fill up the vacancies instead of hiring Jos or maximize the services of available personnel so as not to incur additional expenses;
The City Accountant should observe stringent fiscal administration in the proper classification of accounts;
Require the submission of accomplishment reports as basis for payment. Utilize the services of the permanent employees in discharging regular/ordinary services to compensate and maximize  the costs of their employment.

We recommended that:

The SP members should explain why the excess RATA they received in view of their absences incurred, may not be disallowed in audit; 
The City Treasury Office should secure a certification on the attendance of the Honorable Body from the SB Secretary as basis for the payment of RATA;

The City should strictly adhere to the provisions of existing laws, rules and regulations regarding the payment of RATA of members of the local sanggunian; and 

The legislative body should prepare a work schedule or performance standards in compliance to DBM LBC No. 102 dated January 17, 2013, as amended by DBM LBC No. 103 dated May 15, 2013 to facilitate the audit of payments of their RATA.

